Dia. 01 Pae or bik
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par What happens if Black attacks from 1?
\par \cf1\b White 2 \cf0\b0 becomes \cf2\b sente \cf0\b0 then\cf2\b  \cf0\b0 Black has to play at 3.
\par
\par After White plays hane at 4, the \cf2\b situation\cf0\b0  becomes \cf2\b critical\cf0\b0 .
\par If Black plays at 5, White makes pae with 6.
\par If Black plays dansu at 6 instead of 5, it becomes gote bik which is not a good result for Black.
\par }
