Dia. 02 Same
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par How about Black 1?
\par After White 2, Black's descending move at 3 looks good, but after White's hane at 4 the pae is unavoidable up to 6.
\par
\par This result is same with the previous diagram. Then does it mean that Black should have answered White's pae threat?
\par No. Black has a good move to capture White.
\par }
