Dia. 03 Bik
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Sometimes it is good to attack from the outside. Shall we try this time as well?
\par So Black starts with 1.
\par
\par After that White has to take with 2, then Black 3 and White 4 are necessary moves.
\par
\par It becomes \cf1\b bik \cf0\b0 up to 7. This is a\cf2\b  failure for Black\cf0\b0  again, which means Black 1 was bad.
\par }
